<h3>The Content Velocity Ratio</h3>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Content velocity ratio comparison across manual, semi-automated, and fully engineered teams" src="/images/blog/content-velocity-ratio-comparison.webp" /></p>
<p>The most useful single metric for content engineering is the content velocity ratio:</p>
<p><strong>Content Velocity Ratio = Articles Published / Full-Time Equivalent Writers</strong></p>
<p>Industry benchmarks:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Manual teams (no engineering):</strong> 2 to 4 articles per FTE per month</li>
<li><strong>Semi-automated teams:</strong> 8 to 15 articles per FTE per month</li>
